title: Malta Employment Change
description: Employment in Malta increased by 1.60 in June of 2022. Employment Change in Malta averaged 0.75 percent from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 2.50 percent in the first quarter of 2017 and a record low of -1.40 percent in the fourth quarter of 2002. In Malta, employment change refers to the quarterly change in the number of persons who work for pay or profit, or perform unpaid family work. Estimates include both full-time and part-time employment. This page provides - Malta Employment Change- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: EUROSTAT
